[Student "S"]
{Stayman convention works just fine after a 2NT opening, just at a higher level.

NORTH knows that 6 points will be enough for game opposite SOUTH's 20-21, she just 
needs to find out if there is a 4-4 Major suit fit. There is, in \Ss.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "4"]
[Dealer "W"]
[Vulnerable "All"]
[Deal "W:AJT.K9.A872.AT96 K3.Q652.K943.KQ7 Q9874.AJT83.Q6.5 652.74.JT5.J8432"]
[Declarer "W"]
[Contract "4S"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "W"]
1NT pass 2H pass 2S pass 4H pass 4S pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 4, chOption: W, chBasis: N, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:3, nBasis: 0, nRot: 3, useStandardVul: true"]
[VersionToken "04c19f10f1a82d9d43c96996e053b988fec8f772cf3146ffd5313e51d60d009a"]
[Category "Partnership Bidding"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "partnership_bidding/stayman_transfers"]
[Student "S"]
{EAST has five cards in each Major and WEST opens 1NT.

First EAST bids 2\H, indicating a 5-card \S suit with the Transfer bid. 
Then, after WEST bids the obligatory 2\S, EAST jumps to 4\H, promising 
enough strength for game, and also five \Hs to go with the five \Ss.

WEST prefers \Ss, so she corrects the contract to 4\S.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "5"]
[Dealer "N"]
[Vulnerable "NS"]
[Deal "N:A96.KQ62.K532.K8 JT87.A94.QJ6.T52 KQ542.87.A8.Q764 3.JT53.T974.AJ93"]
[Declarer "N"]
[Contract "4S"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "N"]
1NT pass 2H pass 2S pass 3NT pass 4S pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 5, chOption: N, chBasis: S, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:0, nBasis: 2, nRot: 2, useStandardVul: true"]
[VersionToken "ef7600392606ab185b20dc34c8d664259bce37145450f45041c9b5973a3836f4"]
[Category "Partnership Bidding"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "partnership_bidding/stayman_transfers"]
[Student "S"]
{With 12 points and five \Ss, when SOUTH hears her partner open 1NT she knows 
there is a game - either 3NT or 4\S.

SOUTH first transfers NORTH to \Ss, then jumps to 3NT, giving NORTH the choice. 

NORTH has three \Ss, so he chooses 4\S, taking the 8-card Major fit.}

